node.text: @breezyjacks shows us how to use summer corn for a sweet treat to beat! Grilled corn cobs and citrus zest give this sweet corn ice cream a perfect blend of sweet and savory flavor. Top it off with caramel corn and you're ready for pure summer bliss!

node.title: Sweet Corn Ice Cream with Caramel Corn

Homemade salted caramel is stirred into melted chocolate, then whipped with egg whites and cream for a fluffy texture with a sweet and salty flavor. Pro-tip: Using chocolate with a higher cocoa content will result in a rich, deep chocolate flavor. 
Full recipe in the link in bio! 🍨🍫

node.text:
Homemade gnocchi sounds tricky, but the actual process is pretty easy — and well worth the effort. After boiling, peeling, and mashing some potatoes, you’ll whisk them with an egg to make the “dough”. Then comes the fun, soothing part: put on your favorite playlist or podcast while you knead, cut, and add little indentations to every piece. Once they’re done, you simply boil them for 30 seconds and fry up in a decadent butter-sage sauce (or a sauce of your choosing.) Restaurant-level gnocchi accomplished!

Click the link in bio to shop the recipe!
